      "content": "thanks, SNR sounds like a good way to frame it in my discussion section. it's just frustrating because the noise feels so... unorganized. like it's not just random math error, but almost like something is actively interfering with the stability of the measurements. do you think there's a way to model that kind of erratic, unpredictable interference in stats, or is it always just treated as white noise?",
